HEADWORD: Dyspeptone
<hw>Dys*pep"tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>dys-</ets> + <ets>peptone</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld>
<def>An insoluble albuminous body formed from casein and other proteid
substances by the action of gastric juice.</def>
<rj><au>Meissner.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
